						Hail, Aradia, from the Amalthean horn Pour forth thy store of Love. I lowly
						bend Before Thee! I invoke thee at the end When other Gods are fallen and
						put to scorn. Thy foot is to my lips! My sighs inborn Rise, touch, curl
